<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97181858817373></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97181858817373><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97181858817373>RE: The Shaman for Casual Players</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97181858817373#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1372 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 17th 5:36 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.37]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>One of the most overlooked places is in the West Commonlands area.&nbsp;&nbsp;Go to the orc camp located on the north wall and face the camp.  Just on your right there is a ridge that goes up to the top along the north face of the wall. At the very top there is a flat area which is completely safe from any wandering mobs and where you can med/heal in comfort.<br>At level 6 you can take down an orc centurian with some difficulty, but the key is to use your spells wisely.<br>The secret to doing this is understanding how the orcs socialize with each other.  The easternmost orc is next to a fire and tent all by himself.  He is not associated in any way with the 5 other orcs at the camp.  The middle 2 two are buddies and help each other out, and the westernmost 3 orcs are a squad by themselves.<br>After you med and buff yourself, ease out onto the top of the ridgeline just far enough where you can see around the tree to target the lone eastern orc.  Cast either "Sicken" or "Drowsy" and immediately run back up to the top of the flat spot against the north wall.  (Let's call that "home"!  :D  )    At this time the orc should just be coming over the lip of the hill towards you.  Go to autoattack and time it so you can cast the other spell I mentioned on the orc.  Cast "Frost Strike" as your mana allows and melle the orc down to the kill.<br>Once he is dead get up and do it again after you heal/med and it spawns.  Other groups or people won't be able to see you up there, so you might have to go down periodically and let them know you are camping the single spawn.<br>As you gain levels you can begin to take the double spawn and then the triple spawn.  The Deathfist belts the orcs drop bring in some fairly decent coin from other players, so the money is quite good.  When you reach level 9 and you have SoW memmed advertise that you are at the orc camp and will trade it for money or "Breeze", since high level characters pass right by the orc camp on their way to High Pass and Kithicor Forest.<br>Hmmmmm, what else?  Oh yeah:<br>You can remain here comfortably till you reach level 12.<br>Remember to get bound in West Freeport.<br>Avoid the orc legionaires till the higher levels.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9950694299473></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9950694299473><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9950694299473>RE: The Shaman for Casual Players</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9950694299473#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=72364><span id= >Camthorn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 13th 8:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>BEGIN QUOTE: Go to the orc camp located on the north wall and face the camp. Just on your right there is a ridge that goes up to the top along the north face of the wall. At the very top there is a flat area which is completely safe from any wandering mobs and where you can med/heal in comfort. <br>END QUOTE:<br><br>This is not strictly true, I'm not sure if it was at the time of writing or not, but it isn't anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are creatures who path through this little plateau. Notably there is the Orc Legionaire who will spawn in the middle section of the camp, and if there are no other players killing the rest of the camp, will wander off, often heading right through this little area.  Secondly, and far more dangerous, is the rare spawn of a werewolf. It comes down the hill opposite this plateau, crosses through the center portion of the camp and passes up through the suggested hunting spot.  I've only seen one in three levels of hunting this orc camp, but it's something to be aware of as they are extremely aggressive and powerful.  Luckily you can turn and run to the druid rings for help most of the time and if you have SoW on you should survive.<br><br>Steven<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
